{"id":"308578964_Mechanistic_insights_into_sodium_storage_in_hard_carbon_anodes_using_local_structure_probes","abstract":"Operando(23)Na solid-state NMR and pair distribution function analysis experiments provide insights into the structure of hard carbon anodes in sodium-ion batteries. Capacity results from \"diamagnetic\" sodium ions first adsorbing onto pore surfaces, defects and between expanded layers, before pooling into larger quasi-metallic clusters/expanded carbon sheets at lower voltages.","authors":["Joshua M Stratford","Phoebe Allan","Oliver Pecher","Philip Chater"],"meta":["October 2016Chemical Communications 52(84)","DOI:10.1039/C6CC06990H"],"references":["283239499_Review-Hard_Carbon_Negative_Electrode_Materials_for_Sodium-Ion_Batteries","273940344_Ab_initio_study_of_sodium_intercalation_into_disordered_carbon","282316993_New_Insights_into_the_Structure_of_Nanoporous_Carbons_from_NMR_Raman_and_Pair_Distribution_Function_Analysis","280691549_New_Mechanistic_Insights_on_Na-Ion_Storage_in_Non-Graphitizable_Carbon","263959987_Ring_Current_Effects_Factors_Affecting_the_NMR_Chemical_Shift_of_Molecules_Adsorbed_on_Porous_Carbons","263213521_Ring_currents","257225407_NMR_study_for_electrochemically_inserted_Na_in_hard_carbon_electrode_of_sodium_ion_battery","256664214_In_Situ_Solid-State_NMR_Spectroscopy_of_Electrochemical_Cells_Batteries_Supercapacitors_and_Fuel_Cells","244686701_The_Mechanisms_of_Lithium_and_Sodium_Insertion_in_Carbon_Materials","244685877_An_In_Situ_Small-Angle_X-Ray_Scattering_Study_of_Sodium_Insertion_into_a_Nanoporous_Carbon_Anode_Material_within_an_Operating_Electrochemical_Cell"]}